message: "If you reference A2A Commerce in academic or technical work, please cite as follows."
title: "A2A Commerce Specification: The Fifth Paradigm of Electronic Commerce"
abstract: >-
  A2A Commerce (Agent-to-Agent Commerce) is the fifth paradigm of electronic
  commerce, in which both buyer and seller are represented by autonomous AI
  Agents acting under human-delegated authority. This specification defines
  the paradigm, its terminology, maturity model (ACML), transaction protocol,
  trust framework, interoperability standards, and economic model.
